WEBVTT

00:02.850 --> 00:08.756
you're listening to a teaching from Reality LA.

00:08.776 --> 00:16.264
Acts 14, again, if you haven't been with us, I'll just give you a very, very brief synopsis of the previous 13 chapters.

00:18.867 --> 00:25.814
So the mission of Jesus, that everyone would know him and be restored to God through him, has been given over to his disciples.

00:25.854 --> 00:29.458
Some of those disciples ended up in a city called Antioch.

00:29.698 --> 00:34.927
Antioch is just a little bit south of Jerusalem and that church was having a prayer meeting.

00:35.748 --> 00:48.690
In that prayer meeting they discerned by the Spirit of God that he was calling a group of their leaders to go overseas and share the good news of Jesus with people beyond their region who had never heard it before.

00:48.802 --> 00:51.124
Two of those leaders were named Paul and Barnabas.

00:51.184 --> 00:52.586
They would be the leaders of their group.

00:52.606 --> 00:53.827
You're gonna hear their names a lot.

00:54.408 --> 00:59.473
So in Acts chapter 14, we hear about most of that first journey, though not all of it.

00:59.513 --> 01:00.754
We covered some of it in chapter 13.

01:01.615 --> 01:06.300
But in 14, we hear about three different cities that are in modern day Turkey.

01:06.320 --> 01:09.883
We're gonna see them experience some opposition to the gospel.

01:10.424 --> 01:14.087
So that's my short synopsis of Acts chapters one to 13.

01:14.127 --> 01:16.690
Now, chapter 14,

01:17.058 --> 01:19.502
I will read and then pray, Acts 14.

01:24.511 --> 01:37.874
Now at Iconium, they entered together into a Jewish synagogue and spoke in such a way that a great number of both Jews and Greeks believed, but the unbelieving Jews stirred up the Gentiles and poisoned their minds against the brothers.

01:38.795 --> 01:40.498
So they remained for a long time.

01:40.770 --> 01:47.661
Speaking boldly for the Lord, who bore witness to the word of His grace, granting signs and wonders to be done by their hands.

01:48.482 --> 01:52.929
But the people of the city were divided, some sided with the Jews and some with the apostles.

01:53.610 --> 02:04.066
When an attempt was made by both Gentiles and Jews with their rulers to mistreat them and stone them, they learned of it and fled to Lystra and Derby.

02:05.208 --> 02:09.394
Cities in Lyconia, we'll go with Lyconia.

02:10.626 --> 02:12.108
and to the surrounding country.

02:12.428 --> 02:14.851
And there they continued to preach the gospel.

02:15.972 --> 02:20.898
Now at Leistra, there was a man sitting who could not use his feet.

02:21.478 --> 02:23.400
He was crippled from birth and had never walked.

02:24.461 --> 02:39.218
He listened to Paul speaking and Paul looking intently at him and seeing that he had faith to be made well said in a loud voice, stand upright on your feet and he sprang up and began walking.

02:39.874 --> 02:48.947
And when the crowds saw what Paul had done, they lifted up their voices, saying in Laconian, the gods have come down to us in the likeness of men.

02:49.007 --> 02:54.836
Barnabas, they called Zeus and Paul, they called Hermes because he was the chief speaker.

02:55.717 --> 03:04.690
And the priest of Zeus, whose temple was at the entrance of the city, brought oxen and garlands to the gates and wanted to offer sacrifice with the crowds.

03:05.442 --> 03:14.456
but when the apostles, Barnabas and Paul heard of it, they tore their garments and rushed into the crowd, crying out, men, why are you doing these things?

03:15.257 --> 03:26.495
We are also men of like nature with you, and we bring you good news that you should turn away from these vain things to a living God who made heaven and earth and the sea and all that is in them.

03:26.856 --> 03:30.562
In past generations, he allowed all the nations to walk in their own ways.

03:31.062 --> 03:33.426
Yet he did not leave himself without witness.

03:33.794 --> 03:41.043
For he did good by giving you reigns from heaven and fruitful seasons, satisfying your hearts with food and gladness.

03:42.204 --> 03:46.569
Even with these words, they scarcely restrained the people from offering sacrifice to them.

03:48.071 --> 03:57.723
But Jews came from Antioch and Iconium, and having persuaded the crowds, they stoned Paul and dragged him out of the city, supposing that he was dead.

03:58.944 --> 04:03.730
But when the disciples gathered about him, he rose up and entered the city,

04:03.874 --> 04:07.138
and on the next day went on with Barnabas to Derby.

04:08.560 --> 04:26.682
When they had preached the gospel to that city and had made many disciples, they returned to Lystra and Iconium and Antioch, strengthening the souls of the disciples, encouraging them to continue in the faith and saying that through many tribulations, we must enter the kingdom of God.

04:27.403 --> 04:33.010
And when they had appointed elders for them in every church with prayer and fasting, they committed them to the Lord

04:33.250 --> 04:34.331
in whom they had believed.

04:35.573 --> 04:39.078
Then they passed through Pecidia and came to Pamphylia.

04:39.418 --> 04:43.203
And when they had spoken the word in Perga, they went down to Atelia.

04:43.764 --> 04:50.653
And from there, they sailed to Antioch where they had been commended on the grace of God for the work that they had fulfilled.

04:51.514 --> 05:03.250
And when they arrived and gathered the church together, they declared all that God had done with them and how he had opened a door of faith to the Gentiles, and they remained no little time with the disciples.

05:04.162 --> 05:05.143
This is the word of the Lord.

05:06.605 --> 05:06.965
Let's pray.

05:09.868 --> 05:16.475
Father in heaven, thank you for making us one with yourself through our Lord Jesus Christ.

05:18.217 --> 05:28.508
Thank you that all who call on his name will be saved, filled with your Holy Spirit, and called the partner with you on your mission to make yourself known in this world.

05:30.570 --> 05:33.874
We ask as we look into your word today that you would give us eyes to see.

05:34.626 --> 05:35.387
and ears to hear.

05:37.228 --> 05:38.590
Give his hearts to understand.

05:40.552 --> 05:47.058
God, I ask today that you would give courage to our souls as we go on mission day to day.

05:48.739 --> 05:50.821
As for me, I am your vessel lord.

05:51.181 --> 05:58.168
Let the words of my mouth and the meditations of my heart be pleasing to you, O God, our rock, our redeemer.

05:58.729 --> 06:01.271
And everybody in the church said, amen.

06:02.272 --> 06:04.594
Amen, amen.

06:04.994 --> 06:10.201
Last week, a few days before Christmas, last Sunday, in fact.

06:10.922 --> 06:13.004
A couple of members of our church were baptized.

06:14.026 --> 06:14.647
Very exciting.

06:14.887 --> 06:15.868
It's okay to celebrate that.

06:16.068 --> 06:16.469
There we go.

06:16.850 --> 06:17.250
There it is.

06:18.732 --> 06:19.553
We're figuring it out.

06:19.573 --> 06:20.354
We're waking it up.

06:21.436 --> 06:23.618
A couple members of our church were baptized.

06:23.718 --> 06:27.103
And one of them in a conversation I heard about secondhand.

06:27.123 --> 06:29.326
So this is not a direct quote, but something to the sense.

06:30.267 --> 06:32.530
One of them said, I feel light.

06:32.706 --> 06:35.650
I feel free, I feel ready for the mission.

06:36.151 --> 06:36.632
Let's go.

06:36.652 --> 06:39.917
Woo, that's what's up.

06:40.618 --> 06:42.220
I feel the same way, just saying that.

06:43.502 --> 06:48.550
And that is the exact right feeling, getting out of the baptismal.

06:48.610 --> 06:57.764
That's the compelling vision of the kingdom of God that we've received in the gospel that we're reminded of with every baptism.

06:58.425 --> 07:01.970
It moves us to say, everybody's gotta know.

07:02.946 --> 07:04.227
Everybody's got to know.

07:04.247 --> 07:11.676
This is a natural human response to something that changes you, moves you, that works for your life, right?

07:12.497 --> 07:13.778
We know this instinctively.

07:14.699 --> 07:18.323
We've all heard of keto and crossfit and veganism.

07:18.443 --> 07:21.146
And you've heard about the latest movies that are great.

07:21.527 --> 07:24.910
You've heard about the best Thai food in LA and the best tacos.

07:25.291 --> 07:25.551
Why?

07:26.572 --> 07:31.858
Because when we find something beautiful that delights us, that fills us with joy.

07:32.450 --> 07:35.973
The first thing we wanna do is tell somebody.

07:38.216 --> 07:41.259
And so that is the mission.

07:41.359 --> 07:42.760
It is literally that simple.

07:43.921 --> 07:44.762
Christ has come.

07:45.603 --> 07:46.504
Christ lives.

07:47.204 --> 07:48.846
Christ can set you free.

07:49.627 --> 07:50.828
Now go tell somebody.

07:52.470 --> 07:55.112
This is the mission that each of us has called to, made for.

07:55.172 --> 07:57.094
It's ingrained in our bones.

07:57.495 --> 08:00.978
Followers of Jesus, this is what we're supposed to do.

08:01.058 --> 08:04.184
Day, making disciples of all nations as we go about our lives.

08:05.286 --> 08:08.392
That means showing the love of Christ and telling them the good news.

08:09.394 --> 08:17.830
And as they hear continuing to show and tell, to teach them to obey all Christ is commanded, that's discipleship.

08:17.930 --> 08:22.258
And many of us will do this just on a daily basis.

08:22.722 --> 08:40.420
in seemingly mundane ways, inviting a neighbor to church, helping a family member through a difficult time, raising your children to know and enjoy God, loving your friends in these seemingly simple, dismissible things.

08:41.141 --> 08:42.622
The kingdom of God is breaking through.

08:42.662 --> 08:50.450
And a few of us have, and a few of us will go out into places and among people that we do not yet know,

08:50.690 --> 08:55.415
learning their languages, loving them well, and making disciples of another nation.

08:57.838 --> 09:10.552
And no matter what you're called to, or how you're called to do this, this mission that we're called to with Christ is something all of us are meant to be in.

09:10.652 --> 09:19.122
So whether you're a stay-at-home parent, a business leader, a doctor, a teacher, a pastor, it's all one mission.

09:20.130 --> 09:23.936
and all of us can learn from this group of missionaries in Acts 14.

09:23.956 --> 09:26.560
I could highlight so many things here.

09:26.660 --> 09:28.523
I mean, it's an entire chapter of Scripture.

09:30.066 --> 09:48.114
I could go on about how the mission requires us to know the word that Paul and Barnabas argued boldly and convincingly in a Jewish synagogue where people knew the Scripture and made Christ so clear that these people who thought they knew realized something

09:48.386 --> 09:50.188
new and wonderful that Christ has come.

09:50.949 --> 09:52.751
And he was promised and has fulfilled the Scripture.

09:53.092 --> 10:04.966
I could go on and on about how this chapter shows us that the mission requires wisdom, that you can't minister to a bunch of people who know the word, the same way you minister to people who know nothing about it.

10:06.248 --> 10:12.696
Their ministry in Lystra is completely different from their ministry in Iconium.

10:14.478 --> 10:15.719
And so it requires wisdom.

10:15.779 --> 10:18.002
It requires wisdom to know when to stand up,

10:18.690 --> 10:23.976
and face opposition and when to leave town lest you get stoned.

10:24.496 --> 10:34.167
I could go on and on about how here in this chapter we see the importance of the power of God for it is God who bore witness to the word of his grace by miracles and wonders.

10:35.568 --> 10:43.317
And it is God who made a lame man walk so that people who had never heard the truth of scripture might hear the gospel and be saved.

10:43.397 --> 10:44.498
I could go on

10:44.706 --> 10:57.059
and on about how that power doesn't just belong to super Christians, but everyday disciples, because it was Paul who laid dead, and a group of everyday disciples who gathered around him to pray, and he was raised again.

10:58.601 --> 11:03.947
I could go on and on, but my son reminded me that kids are in the room, and I need to be short.

11:08.031 --> 11:08.592
So I prayed.

11:08.632 --> 11:12.816
I prayed and I asked the Lord, what would you have me focus on today?

11:12.856 --> 11:14.418
What does our church need to hear?

11:16.386 --> 11:23.859
So I'm gonna focus on three things that we see in Acts 14 that are essential for life and mission with Jesus.

11:25.943 --> 11:29.790
Three things in Acts 14 that are essential for life and mission with Jesus.

11:30.291 --> 11:35.921
The first is this, to live on a mission with Jesus in our city and any city is courage.

11:37.103 --> 11:39.026
You need courage.

11:45.570 --> 11:52.779
Imagine the courage that it would take to stand before a group of people who are saying, you are a God.

11:53.180 --> 11:55.303
We will give you all the power you ask for.

11:56.504 --> 11:58.226
Imagine the courage it would take to say, no, no.

11:59.788 --> 12:00.489
I am not God.

12:02.011 --> 12:02.832
Christ is Lord.

12:03.613 --> 12:04.394
Put away your riches.

12:05.315 --> 12:06.056
Put away your power.

12:06.096 --> 12:07.438
I don't want any of it.

12:08.540 --> 12:09.301
Now, God bless you.

12:09.361 --> 12:10.482
You think you could do that.

12:12.834 --> 12:14.497
But money and power are greatly alluring.

12:14.557 --> 12:20.808
Imagine the courage necessary to face the opposition that Paul and Barnumus are facing.

12:21.709 --> 12:24.514
There's a word that gets used in the church a lot.

12:27.540 --> 12:29.002
The word is encouragement.

12:29.022 --> 12:29.764
That was encouraging.

12:30.405 --> 12:31.266
That encouraged me.

12:32.228 --> 12:34.592
And sometimes what we mean is, that made me feel good.

12:37.116 --> 12:38.098
Encouragement

12:38.562 --> 12:40.364
has a very specific meaning.

12:40.504 --> 12:42.787
I don't want you to like start policing how other people use this word.

12:44.388 --> 12:45.610
But you could police how you use it.

12:45.630 --> 12:47.512
Maybe.

12:49.053 --> 12:53.578
Courage comes from the Latin word that means heart.

12:53.598 --> 12:55.541
Heart, will, inner strength.

12:55.941 --> 13:01.227
And so to encourage is to put that heart into other people.

13:02.568 --> 13:04.891
It is literally to put heart in something.

13:06.012 --> 13:07.794
To give someone the will

13:08.194 --> 13:08.755
to go on.

13:10.076 --> 13:16.584
And so, courage is something we can impart to one another.

13:16.624 --> 13:18.426
Courage is something that you can grow in.

13:19.488 --> 13:29.580
Courage, as I remind my children all the time, is not the absence of fear, but having the heart, the willpower, to do what is necessary in spite of fear.

13:31.041 --> 13:33.785
And it's not a thing that belongs only to extraordinary people.

13:34.466 --> 13:38.130
In fact, just right now, take like two seconds and think about

13:38.498 --> 13:41.662
a story of courage that you've read about, heard about, or heard.

13:44.766 --> 13:50.934
It's ordinary people in extraordinary circumstances, doing something uncommon.

13:52.676 --> 13:58.624
Courage is something that belongs to ordinary people because we're all people who need courage.

13:59.725 --> 14:02.289
I love this quote from Ralph Waldo Emerson.

14:03.010 --> 14:06.354
He said, a hero is no braver than any ordinary man.

14:07.042 --> 14:08.664
but he is brave five minutes longer.

14:13.150 --> 14:19.618
And so courage is something all of us can have and we can learn here in Acts 14.

14:19.658 --> 14:28.609
And we need courage because opposition is guaranteed and the danger is real.

14:29.310 --> 14:32.274
Let's look at the courage of Paul and Barnabas first in Iconium.

14:33.410 --> 14:38.215
They go to Iconium and they go first to the synagogue.

14:38.615 --> 14:39.856
And that is for two reasons.

14:40.057 --> 14:43.560
One, because that's where people know the scripture so they can preach the gospel very easily.

14:43.961 --> 14:48.785
Two, in that synagogue would be people who are called God-fearrs.

14:49.206 --> 15:01.298
That is non-Jews, also those Gentiles, that's Gentiles who understand that the God of the Bible is the one true God and they've joined in with the community, but they're not Jewish.

15:02.050 --> 15:07.696
Paul and Barnabas go to the synagogue knowing that those godfearers will be a bridge to the broader culture.

15:08.457 --> 15:10.499
Those godfearers have a foot in both worlds.

15:11.460 --> 15:20.069
And so if we can get them to believe the gospel, if they will turn to Jesus and be saved, they will be an open door into the rest of the city.

15:20.410 --> 15:22.472
So they go and it works.

15:22.972 --> 15:28.338
Some Jews and some Gentiles in the city of Iconium hear the gospel and believe.

15:29.282 --> 15:32.767
but just as quickly opposition rises up.

15:34.830 --> 15:37.154
This opposition here in Iconium is indirect.

15:38.175 --> 15:52.517
Some of the people who oppose the message team up with those who may have been enemies and the government to find ways to do an injustice and mistreat Paul Barnabas and the missionary group that's come with them.

15:55.562 --> 15:58.386
And so it takes great courage from them, but look at what they do.

16:01.122 --> 16:06.570
In verse two, it says, unbelieving Jews stirred up the Gentiles and poisoned their mind against the brothers.

16:07.672 --> 16:18.609
So unbelieving Jews and Gentiles have worked together to convince people that these Christians mean poorly, mean ill for their town.

16:18.649 --> 16:20.271
They've poisoned the minds against them.

16:20.752 --> 16:23.857
So look at what Paul and Barnabas do.

16:24.358 --> 16:29.906
So they remain for a long time speaking boldly for the Lord.

16:31.074 --> 16:32.275
And the Lord does a work.

16:32.316 --> 16:37.602
He bore witness to the word of His grace, granting signs and wonders to be done by their hands.

16:40.606 --> 16:44.190
So the opposition to the Iconium is real, but it's indirect.

16:45.231 --> 16:46.733
And they have the courage to stay.

16:48.015 --> 16:50.057
Now they also have the wisdom to leave when it's time to leave.

16:50.097 --> 16:54.963
So they leave Iconium and they go to Lystra.

16:55.344 --> 17:00.370
Lystra is a different town, despite being in the Roman Empire.

17:00.962 --> 17:06.631
This small town likely spoke Greek and lyestrian.

17:06.811 --> 17:07.712
I don't know how to say that word.

17:08.854 --> 17:09.595
Lyestrian.

17:09.615 --> 17:10.657
We'll go with lyestrian for now.

17:11.658 --> 17:12.720
But there's no synagogue here.

17:12.880 --> 17:21.613
As being in Greek culture, they probably had a marketplace where local philosophers and teachers would teach in the open air, trying to gain more followers.

17:22.134 --> 17:30.226
And so Paul and Barnabas would have joined that square and preached the gospel right next to all of these other ideas in the market.

17:30.690 --> 17:34.096
And it's God's power that moves here.

17:34.476 --> 17:35.658
God's power moves first.

17:35.698 --> 17:41.628
So in Iconium, they met opposition after the Word went forth and then power followed.

17:41.949 --> 17:44.173
In Leistra, God's power moves.

17:45.014 --> 17:49.682
And the first opposition they get is a complete misunderstanding of the message.

17:53.378 --> 18:00.908
Paul and Barnabas narrowly avoid being worshipped as gods, and the missionaries get to work making disciples, but now the real opposition sets in.

18:01.730 --> 18:04.934
This opposition is much more direct.

18:07.878 --> 18:18.973
Sometime after the episode around almost having a bull sacrifice to them, the persecutors from Iconium and from Antioch show up.

18:20.275 --> 18:22.258
People come all the way from other cities.

18:23.010 --> 18:23.991
just to start a fight.

18:25.474 --> 18:31.843
But this time, instead of seeking legal routes, they turned to public opinion and turned the people themselves against the disciples.

18:32.363 --> 18:34.927
This opposition is direct and it is violent.

18:35.448 --> 18:43.740
In the span of a few days, the people who wanted to exalt Paul as a God, drug him out of the city and stoned into death.

18:48.126 --> 18:49.228
What are the disciples gonna do?

18:49.268 --> 18:50.930
Well, they could scatter

18:52.770 --> 19:02.282
They could run away, but in verse 20, when the disciples gathered about him, that is Paul, he rose up and entered the city.

19:06.107 --> 19:11.014
So Paul and Barnabas show us, and then they go to Derby and they preach the gospel and many disciples are made there.

19:11.074 --> 19:20.466
So to recap here, we need courage on the mission because opposition is real, danger is real.

19:21.218 --> 19:23.521
In Iconium, we see indirect opposition.

19:23.581 --> 19:27.326
In Lystra, we see direct and violent opposition.

19:27.667 --> 19:29.389
In Derby, the gospel is received.

19:29.609 --> 19:30.511
Many disciples are made.

19:31.472 --> 19:34.576
Quick side note, preach the gospel, results may vary.

19:37.740 --> 19:38.742
Some will follow Jesus.

19:38.802 --> 19:39.783
Some will turn against you.

19:40.484 --> 19:44.349
Some may try to exalt you as a God, but you don't dictate outcomes.

19:44.910 --> 19:45.951
Your call is to be faithful.

19:47.533 --> 19:50.898
Which in some way, in some ways, is more difficult.

19:51.842 --> 19:52.844
than knowing the outcome.

19:54.045 --> 19:59.434
And so we need courage just to try because we have no idea what's gonna happen.

20:01.196 --> 20:04.782
We need courage just to try because we don't know what's gonna happen.

20:07.166 --> 20:20.466
But danger is real and I wanna briefly point out danger in the global church because it's very easy to forget about with a news cycle that doesn't cover it

20:20.578 --> 20:26.106
and living a pretty comfortable life in a pretty affluent country.

20:28.129 --> 20:43.951
On the island of Bali in Indonesia, right now, Muslim extremists frequently attack Christians in the open with no recourse, and a person converting to Christianity may be ostracized from their family, lose their business, and lose all social standing.

20:45.293 --> 20:46.194
In Kazakhstan,

20:46.818 --> 20:56.149
Christian activity is closely monitored by the government, fined regularly and publicly shamed by the surrounding community.

20:57.811 --> 21:05.019
In various places in Mali, missionaries and pastors are regularly kidnapped and their homes and church buildings are destroyed.

21:06.481 --> 21:14.450
The Vietnamese government sees Christianity as a threat to power and control and so closely monitors all churches at all times

21:14.914 --> 21:22.303
and frequently denies Christians access to basic needs like utilities, social service, and education.

21:23.865 --> 21:25.366
Persecution is a real thing.

21:25.427 --> 21:31.133
It's a thing that Jesus faced, it's a thing that church has faced since the beginning, and it's happening right now.

21:31.294 --> 21:41.746
Unless we get too comfortable, we need to be reminded that we have brothers and sisters across the world in pain and in prison who need our prayers and our support.

21:43.490 --> 21:44.772
And so pray for the nations.

21:46.674 --> 21:50.198
Pray that the Lord would give courage in the face of opposition.

21:51.460 --> 21:54.403
Pray that the Lord would give voice to the martyrs.

21:55.425 --> 22:03.455
If you want more information on how to pray, you can go to voiceofthemarders.com, you can go to frontier missions for specific insights into the Muslim world.

22:05.737 --> 22:12.786
But that danger to the Christian church is still real, though we don't experience on a daily basis.

22:14.018 --> 22:15.000
And so we must pray.

22:19.026 --> 22:28.541
Now, recognizing that danger is real, we also need to acknowledge the danger that we are presently in in our own city.

22:28.641 --> 22:30.043
So a brief word on that.

22:31.406 --> 22:37.415
Because we need courage against constant pressure on the poisoning of the mind.

22:37.455 --> 22:41.842
These are two kinds of opposition that I see both in the text,

22:41.922 --> 22:44.345
Acts 14 and in our own city.

22:45.908 --> 22:48.251
Constant pressure and the poisoning of the mind.

22:49.513 --> 22:56.302
Constant sometimes subtle pressure to abandon Jesus and the teachings of Scripture is prevalent.

22:56.363 --> 23:10.002
In Acts 14 we see it in Iconium when unbelieving Jews stir up the Gentiles when they go to the government and look for ways to mistreat.

23:10.082 --> 23:17.693
The missionaries, we see crowds obviously pressing and stoning, stoning Paul.

23:18.273 --> 23:22.219
This constant pressure is a danger.

23:22.279 --> 23:31.912
Now, here's the difference between, here's why constant pressure is sometimes, sometimes more dangerous than overt direct opposition.

23:32.393 --> 23:38.962
Because if I come at you like this, right, menacingly,

23:39.874 --> 23:40.695
That's menacing, right?

23:40.735 --> 23:43.057
This is scary.

23:43.918 --> 23:50.024
If I come at you like that and I'm just stalking towards you, you're gonna do one of two things.

23:50.044 --> 23:52.326
You're gonna run or you're gonna knuckle up.

23:53.367 --> 23:54.708
Some of y'all need to chill.

23:55.909 --> 23:59.673
But you're gonna know what's coming and you're gonna be ready for that.

24:01.114 --> 24:09.042
Now, imagine the difference between that experience and standing in the courtyard and just having somebody lean on you.

24:10.498 --> 24:11.419
Just put their weight on you.

24:11.580 --> 24:11.860
That's it.

24:14.404 --> 24:26.081
Not a big deal at first, but over time, the strength and energy it takes to assert counter pressure and remain upright wears you out.

24:27.523 --> 24:36.616
You are slowly unknowingly worn down until you've got to change your situation or get pushed over.

24:38.399 --> 24:40.402
I think sometimes living in LA is like that.

24:42.754 --> 24:49.602
It's a constant, sometimes gentle pressure away from Christ.

24:52.425 --> 25:10.226
To conform to the world's way of thinking, our city's way of living, the way people see career, money, relationships, God, other people, leads to a different way of

25:10.498 --> 25:16.264
thinking and speaking of going about our jobs and becomes very difficult to resist.

25:17.565 --> 25:28.536
The love of possessions, love of pleasure, prideful self-focused denial of God's word, it creeps in slowly over time, not all of a sudden.

25:30.197 --> 25:33.140
This effect of living in L.A. is amplified by the internet.

25:35.102 --> 25:39.026
As voices offering, offering counter narratives,

25:39.618 --> 25:49.249
are constantly in our ears, and sometimes we willingly subject ourselves to them, not knowing that they are pushing us ever so gently away from Christ.

25:52.072 --> 25:53.313
This is a danger that we're all in.

25:54.315 --> 25:57.038
And some of us, I think, feel the pressure more than we're aware of.

25:58.399 --> 26:00.742
And it's why getting out of LA is sometimes really helpful.

26:02.103 --> 26:05.127
It's also why being in church on Sunday is extremely helpful.

26:06.408 --> 26:08.050
I spend six days a week

26:08.994 --> 26:09.715
under pressure.

26:11.357 --> 26:13.000
Give me two hours of Jesus.

26:14.281 --> 26:24.316
With his people, at his table, hearing his truth being reminded of who I am, constant, gentle pressure is a danger in our city.

26:25.578 --> 26:37.234
The other danger that I see in this text and in our city is what was described here in verse two, the poisoning of the mind against the brothers.

26:38.338 --> 26:40.760
This is part of, but not the same as the pressure.

26:41.241 --> 26:52.412
It's a slow convincing that the church is against you, that the church is bad, that the church is wrong, a slow poisoning of the mind.

26:54.094 --> 26:55.756
Poisoning of the mind turns us bitter.

26:57.518 --> 27:01.602
Here's why this is different, because sometimes it's other Christians doing it.

27:03.544 --> 27:05.746
Sometimes it's people saying they're Christians.

27:07.202 --> 27:17.337
But they're also telling you who's in and who's out, how to know you're on the right team, and who to stand against, who to condemn.

27:17.377 --> 27:25.269
The slow poisoning the mind stirs up division in Christ's church, and that is way too easy to stir.

27:27.272 --> 27:28.574
And it's rampant in our culture.

27:31.499 --> 27:36.466
It seems like people enjoy provoking hatred against the church.

27:39.394 --> 27:45.163
But my friends, do not engage with this kind of stuff.

27:47.186 --> 27:50.090
Whispers of distrust do not bring reconciliation.

27:51.352 --> 27:54.496
Open, humble conversations will.

27:54.517 --> 28:00.606
Passing rumors will not bring peace, but gentle confrontation of wrongdoing will.

28:02.288 --> 28:08.978
Using uncharitable language to discuss this pastor, that congregation, will only deepen the divides that already

28:09.986 --> 28:14.393
That already I say with tears exist all too often in the global church.

28:18.739 --> 28:27.793
Few of us will face the kind of persecution that the Iconians and the Lyestrians brought against Paul and Barnabas in our lifetime.

28:29.256 --> 28:30.618
But we need to be ready for it.

28:31.800 --> 28:35.565
And we prepare for it by knowing the danger that we're in right now.

28:37.228 --> 28:38.610
By looking to Christ.

28:40.674 --> 28:52.252
by not being afraid, by living courageously against the constant gentle pressure and the messages that would poison our mind against God and his people.

28:54.255 --> 29:03.509
To live on mission with Jesus requires courage because the danger is real, though not often obvious.

29:06.894 --> 29:09.458
But that courage cannot be fostered in isolation.

29:10.274 --> 29:15.559
You may have drove here today by yourself, but you are not in a room by yourself.

29:16.741 --> 29:26.310
And so I will observe the second thing that I feel led to in this text that we need for the mission of God is community.

29:28.152 --> 29:32.337
To live on mission with Jesus, you need courage and you need community.

29:34.078 --> 29:37.522
Life on mission is not about you becoming a spiritual John Wick.

29:38.946 --> 29:44.772
running all over town, speaking boldly, telling this guy to get up and walk, telling that girl to see.

29:44.812 --> 30:07.954
Life on mission with Jesus is about making disciples, doing the long, slow work, of teaching them to follow Jesus, love one another and serve our city, that they could together, as a community, would be a perpetual display of the love of Christ to their city.

30:09.698 --> 30:15.625
Paul knew that, Barnabas knew that, and that's why they were committed, not to just make converts, but disciples.

30:19.030 --> 30:21.713
So to live on mission with Jesus, you need community.

30:22.314 --> 30:27.360
And lest I make this strictly about a program, I'm gonna talk about it this in two ways.

30:27.760 --> 30:32.186
You need to invest in the community, and you need to receive from the community.

30:34.068 --> 30:37.793
I'm just gonna tell you at the outset, for some of you, one of these is gonna be really hard.

30:37.813 --> 30:38.834
It's gonna be the invest.

30:39.906 --> 30:42.971
For others of you, the receive part's gonna be hard.

30:43.492 --> 30:44.934
Just stick with me all the way through.

30:48.119 --> 30:50.323
You need community, you need to invest in community.

30:50.363 --> 30:53.007
Paul and Barnabas are obviously doing that.

30:54.269 --> 30:59.538
It wouldn't take a lot of work for me to unpack, it would take a long time for me to unpack all of the ways.

30:59.682 --> 31:00.423
that they're doing that.

31:00.443 --> 31:03.288
And it wouldn't take a lot of work for you to notice them as you read.

31:03.608 --> 31:06.112
Paul and Barnabas go to people they don't know.

31:06.152 --> 31:08.175
They stay when things get hard.

31:08.536 --> 31:12.902
They continually encourage as things get increasingly difficult.

31:13.203 --> 31:17.990
They stay long enough to teach them not just what to think but how to practice.

31:18.110 --> 31:21.255
We notice that they pray and fast together.

31:21.656 --> 31:25.682
So there is a lived practice together that they're doing as a community.

31:26.850 --> 31:32.095
The summary of the mission in Derby, I think, is the peak example of their investment in the community.

31:32.115 --> 31:34.298
They preached the gospel and made many disciples.

31:35.699 --> 31:40.164
Preaching the gospel is easy.

31:41.866 --> 31:43.808
Making disciples takes time.

31:45.309 --> 31:50.034
A disciple is not someone who answers an altar call and then goes right back to the way they were living life before.

31:50.835 --> 31:53.938
A disciple of Jesus is a student of his way of life.

31:54.562 --> 31:59.451
A disciple draws near to Christ, learns from Christ and becomes like Christ.

32:01.815 --> 32:10.772
Many disciples were made, tells us Paul and Barnabas stayed there until they knew this is a community who knows how to do this without us.

32:12.415 --> 32:18.546
This is a community that knows the way of Jesus and can live it and tell the city about it.

32:25.090 --> 32:25.951
I don't know what that means.

32:26.572 --> 32:27.973
I wrote something down, I don't know what it means.

32:30.976 --> 32:31.097
Sorry.

32:31.117 --> 32:31.457
Oh, yes.

32:31.677 --> 32:48.115
Okay, so if their commitment through stoning and riots and threats and government persecution, if that's not clear, if that doesn't make their commitment clear to you, check out verses 21 to 23.

32:48.596 --> 32:49.196
I'll read it again.

32:50.197 --> 32:50.878
Or you can look at it.

32:51.379 --> 32:54.482
When they had preached the gospel to that city, Derby,

32:54.562 --> 33:01.252
and it made many disciples, they returned to Lystra and Iconium and Antioch.

33:01.873 --> 33:07.321
They returned to Lystra, Iconium and Antioch.

33:07.642 --> 33:12.409
Those people want to kill you guys, but they returned.

33:12.950 --> 33:13.310
Why?

33:13.350 --> 33:23.826
To strengthen the souls of the disciples, encourage them to continue the faith and saying through many tribulations, you must enter the kingdom of God.

33:25.282 --> 33:33.161
They returned in the face of mortal danger to encourage, because you need courage for the mission.

33:35.527 --> 33:41.682
They returned likely to answer questions, respond to doubts,

33:41.986 --> 33:51.317
give comfort to those going through difficulty, teaching again about the kingdom of God, reinforcing the practices of faith, like worship, fasting, and prayer.

33:51.357 --> 33:59.407
They return to give strength to the hearts of those who believe so that they would continue in the faith.

34:01.309 --> 34:04.553
They invest despite the cost to themselves.

34:07.577 --> 34:11.762
Because these are Christ's people, and we don't get to pick.

34:12.386 --> 34:14.789
who he loves and calls us to love.

34:18.553 --> 34:26.503
They even go so far, their commitment goes beyond all of that, going back to Antioch, the church that had sent them out on this journey.

34:27.444 --> 34:30.027
Paul and Barnabas show commitment to that local church.

34:30.087 --> 34:32.290
They testify and give all honor to the Lord.

34:33.311 --> 34:35.634
Look, this is what God has done.

34:35.654 --> 34:39.218
And they remain no little time with the disciples there.

34:41.474 --> 34:46.299
The commitment to community is a commitment to the local church.

34:46.359 --> 34:52.366
These spots, they weren't just like, it wasn't like a Bible study over there and a prayer group over here.

34:52.406 --> 34:53.587
There weren't that many Christians.

34:53.888 --> 34:54.668
They were all here.

34:55.009 --> 34:56.190
This is all of us, that's it.

34:57.191 --> 35:07.042
And so this local church, to commit to the local church is to commit to the mission because the mission goes forth from the local church and builds up the local church.

35:09.184 --> 35:10.866
As you go out and make disciples,

35:11.106 --> 35:12.768
Those disciples join a local church.

35:12.848 --> 35:16.052
That local church equips, encourages comforts and corrects them.

35:16.393 --> 35:17.634
They learn to make disciples.

35:17.654 --> 35:18.655
They go out and make disciples.

35:18.695 --> 35:19.997
Those disciples join the local church.

35:20.358 --> 35:21.419
It doesn't have to be here.

35:21.779 --> 35:22.901
I don't care where you go to church.

35:23.141 --> 35:24.383
I just want you to follow Jesus.

35:24.703 --> 35:25.404
Here's what I'm saying.

35:25.764 --> 35:28.107
The local church is essential to the mission.

35:29.509 --> 35:31.211
And the mission builds the local church.

35:32.853 --> 35:34.315
Jesus said, go.

35:34.355 --> 35:36.578
And so we go together.

35:38.721 --> 35:39.922
Paul and Barnabas,

35:40.034 --> 35:45.462
are not solo missionaries, they go together and they build up the local church.

35:56.197 --> 35:58.701
Paul and Barnabas are good examples of investing in the local church.

35:58.721 --> 36:04.850
They're constantly building it up at cost of their own selves, but they're also good examples of receiving from the local church.

36:05.410 --> 36:10.938
It's really easy to think of the apostles, these leading men in the church as not needing anything.

36:11.919 --> 36:23.476
But guys, Paul was dead and it was the disciples who rallied around him and prayed and he got back up.

36:26.300 --> 36:28.824
In fact, you can see the support that they get throughout this passage.

36:29.645 --> 36:32.850
News of the conspiracies at Iconium would have been passed by someone.

36:33.698 --> 36:38.323
Safe travel from one town to another would have been supported and provided for.

36:38.624 --> 36:47.274
They were going to places where there would not be ample lodging, but they would receive what was given to them by local disciples.

36:49.456 --> 36:57.746
The whole trip was financed by the church in Antioch, sent and supported by a local church.

36:58.018 --> 37:01.502
Paul and Barnabas are constantly receiving help and support.

37:01.782 --> 37:07.990
Later in life, Paul would even write letters to churches he planted and thank them and bless them for their ongoing support.

37:09.071 --> 37:11.854
Because without them, his ministry wouldn't work.

37:12.375 --> 37:18.502
Now, in case you're not familiar, the them he's writing to are people that wouldn't have heard the gospel without Paul.

37:19.944 --> 37:25.330
And so the church is a kid's big word, write it down, reciprocal community.

37:27.394 --> 37:32.542
It's a reciprocal community where needs are met one by another.

37:35.487 --> 37:44.582
The commitment to the local church, the commitment to the community of faith is recognizing, I need as much as I give and I give as much as I need.

37:46.825 --> 37:49.810
And where everybody's ready to give, everybody's needs are met.

37:55.234 --> 37:58.637
and realizing that the stuff I skipped on the previous page belongs right here.

37:58.877 --> 37:59.578
So I'm just gonna go back.

38:03.322 --> 38:12.210
And because of that, because the church is a place where those who are receiving are also giving and vice versa, we have to go together.

38:13.411 --> 38:13.912
We have to.

38:15.873 --> 38:19.096
Because I have needs that I can't fill myself.

38:20.097 --> 38:23.160
And God is likely not gonna drop them out of the sky.

38:23.180 --> 38:25.042
He's gonna use y'all.

38:27.138 --> 38:32.223
And similarly, you have things that me and my family can provide.

38:33.584 --> 38:37.108
And so rather than poof, it appears on your doorstep.

38:38.809 --> 38:41.913
It appears on your doorstep because we're the ones who dropped it off.

38:43.594 --> 38:49.440
It is God moving through the local church that continually builds us up and we need this.

38:49.500 --> 38:55.666
We must go together because it's with real people in the flesh that we learn to live as Jesus commanded us to.

38:56.674 --> 38:58.837
You cannot learn to forgive by yourself.

39:00.980 --> 39:09.711
You need people who are gonna hurt you so that you can learn to forgive and receive forgiveness because you've hurt them too.

39:11.333 --> 39:24.370
It's with the local church, the commitment to the community, investing in and receiving from, that we learn to pray, serve, love, heal, bear witness to Christ and rejoice in all circumstances.

39:28.418 --> 39:34.485
The church is not a gym that you sign up to be a member of, too.

39:35.365 --> 39:37.988
And you set personal goals for your personal strengths.

39:38.749 --> 39:40.831
And as soon as those aren't being met, you dip out.

39:42.533 --> 39:48.179
The church is a formational community where we enter in together saying, I need help.

39:50.041 --> 39:50.742
Maybe I can help.

39:52.644 --> 39:58.290
We say both simultaneously that all needs might be met and we might grow up together into the likeness of Christ.

40:02.754 --> 40:14.570
We invest in and administer to others, brothers and sisters who can help us, friends in hard seasons, urging us in prayer and on mission.

40:16.913 --> 40:19.777
To live on mission with Jesus, we need each other.

40:21.580 --> 40:26.586
We need pastors, we need deacons, we need brothers and sisters.

40:31.513 --> 40:32.114
Who will

40:32.450 --> 40:39.118
encourage us and give us the heart to go on when we're so tired of praying for the same people and nothing happening.

40:40.540 --> 40:44.925
When we're so tired of serving and showing kindness to people who will not receive it.

40:46.407 --> 40:58.161
When we're so tired of trying to be genuine and gracious to our bosses and our coworkers and all they give us back is vitriol.

41:00.204 --> 41:01.906
We need people around us

41:02.114 --> 41:03.496
to encourage us.

41:03.597 --> 41:07.844
And so to live on mission with Jesus, you need courage and you need community.

41:09.166 --> 41:17.039
But greatest of all, you need Christ without whom you will have neither courage nor community.

41:18.381 --> 41:19.824
We need Christ.

41:22.248 --> 41:28.178
To live on mission with Jesus, you need to go with him in his presence.

41:32.674 --> 41:35.018
Kids, what's Christmas about?

41:36.700 --> 41:37.982
Somebody, any kids, just holler at me.

41:38.302 --> 41:38.963
What's Christmas about?

41:41.387 --> 41:41.768
Say it again.

41:43.610 --> 41:46.254
Spending time with your family, that's what we do on Christmas, love that.

41:46.996 --> 41:51.342
Jesus was born, and so we spend time with our family to rejoice in that fact.

41:52.103 --> 41:53.405
Jesus was born.

41:53.886 --> 41:55.528
Jesus being born means what?

41:56.650 --> 41:59.314
Emmanuel, God with us.

42:01.890 --> 42:05.274
God is with us, and so we go.

42:05.534 --> 42:07.757
God is with us, and so we have courage.

42:08.017 --> 42:16.807
God is with us, and so we have our people, and when we forget that God is with us, we can look at the people around us and remember their stories.

42:17.468 --> 42:19.270
Remember the way he's used them in our lives.

42:19.610 --> 42:24.916
Remember the way he has revealed himself to us through them.

42:24.956 --> 42:29.842
And when all else fails, we can look at each other and say, I need you to tell me again.

42:30.914 --> 42:38.363
because today my heart is faint and I need more of Christ to go on mission with Jesus.

42:39.184 --> 42:40.746
Don't forget about Jesus.

42:43.409 --> 42:57.106
I think that this one thing is why we get so tired of praying and sharing the gospel because we do it on our own strength and we forget to go with Christ.

43:00.002 --> 43:02.125
thousands of years before Jesus walked the earth.

43:02.245 --> 43:07.651
Moses, the man of God, stood in God's presence as God was telling them to go.

43:07.671 --> 43:13.278
And Moses said, if you don't go with us, I'm not going.

43:16.582 --> 43:23.009
The beginning of mission is the point of all mission, to know God and enjoy Him.

43:24.791 --> 43:26.994
Do you today lack courage?

43:28.674 --> 43:30.176
Do you lack community?

43:31.839 --> 43:32.620
Are you hurting?

43:34.202 --> 43:35.464
Do you have questions?

43:36.826 --> 43:39.129
Do you need a guide to help you along the way?

43:40.952 --> 43:43.575
Do you doubt and fear?

43:45.358 --> 43:46.580
Come to Christ.

43:48.823 --> 43:50.625
Come to Christ our healer.

43:50.946 --> 43:52.628
Come to Christ our advocate.

43:52.668 --> 43:54.070
Come to Christ our shepherd.

43:55.412 --> 43:56.594
Come to Christ.

43:58.594 --> 43:59.816
the king of heaven and earth.

43:59.856 --> 44:06.565
There is nothing he will ask you to do that he has not already done himself.

44:08.227 --> 44:12.413
There is nothing Jesus will ask you to do on his mission that he has not already done.

44:12.673 --> 44:17.119
He left his home into heavenly places to become a child and a poor family.

44:17.340 --> 44:21.165
He traveled across borders and learned different languages.

44:21.245 --> 44:23.288
He endured hardships and temptations.

44:23.568 --> 44:25.010
He loved difficult people.

44:27.682 --> 44:30.686
He preached hard words to hard hearts.

44:32.689 --> 44:35.834
He confronted authority with humility and grace.

44:37.336 --> 44:38.318
He humbled himself.

44:39.800 --> 44:45.348
He endured all to the death, even death on a cross.

44:47.571 --> 44:50.375
He was exposed and shamed openly.

44:52.819 --> 44:54.962
He was wounded for our transgressions.

44:59.778 --> 45:03.147
Christ was crucified because of us.

45:04.571 --> 45:06.897
We were the opposition to His mission.

45:08.742 --> 45:14.738
We were the ones bringing persecution when all He brought His love

45:18.722 --> 45:27.612
And as he was being nailed on the cross, offering himself to die for our sins, he did not shed curses upon us or secretly wish harm or look for a way out.

45:27.932 --> 45:31.216
He prayed one simple thing, Father, forgive them.

45:31.937 --> 45:33.158
They don't know what they're doing.

45:37.903 --> 45:42.909
And now for those who have come to faith in him by his stripes, we are healed.

45:45.271 --> 45:47.794
The baby born in a manger has become the Lamb of God.

45:49.570 --> 45:51.332
than the risen king over heaven and earth.

45:52.333 --> 45:55.936
Christ crucified has defeated death.

45:55.976 --> 45:58.499
He is alive.

45:58.539 --> 46:00.801
He is on the throne.

46:00.841 --> 46:04.345
He is praying for you and he is on the move.

46:04.705 --> 46:07.748
To live with him is to be on the move with him.

46:09.049 --> 46:10.591
And he is calling you to himself.

46:10.951 --> 46:13.674
So come and let him fill your heart with courage.

46:15.235 --> 46:17.778
Come and let him fill your life with community.

46:18.818 --> 46:25.313
With all of its beauties and hardships, come to Christ, follow Him on mission.

46:27.398 --> 46:33.453
He will go with you, always, even to the end of the age.

46:36.861 --> 46:37.362
Let's pray.

46:44.738 --> 46:48.962
Father in Heaven, thank you for your Son, Jesus Christ, who has died and risen again that we might live.

46:50.404 --> 46:56.089
And thank you for making the enemies of that story, your friends, your sons and daughters.

46:57.471 --> 46:59.333
Thank you for bringing us here.

47:02.456 --> 47:07.661
And God, as we respond to your word, I ask that you would move in our hearts and teach us to pray.

47:09.503 --> 47:12.786
Teach us to pray that we would understand how to go with you on mission.

47:15.170 --> 47:21.292
God give us ears to hear and eyes to see.

47:21.995 --> 47:26.130
Amen.

